# Production Environment Variables Template
# Copy this to your Vercel project settings: Settings > Environment Variables

# Supabase Configuration
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-public-anon-key-here

# How to find these values:
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Go to Settings > API
# 4. Copy "Project URL" as VITE_SUPABASE_URL
# 5. Copy "anon/public" key as VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES:
# - NEVER use service_role key on the frontend
# - Only use the public anon key (it's safe for client-side use)
# - These variables are exposed in the browser bundle
# - All sensitive operations should be in Supabase Edge Functions with proper auth
